faq:
  - q: "What is the difference between the three training formats?"
    a: "All three formats (4 weeks, 8 weeks, 18 weeks) lead to the same Yoga Alliance RYT-200 certification with identical curriculum and teachers. The difference is the pace: 4-week is full-time intensive, 8-week is semi-intensive, and 18-week can be taken alongside work or studies."
  - q: "What does the 200-hour training curriculum include?"
    a: "The training covers Hatha Yoga, Vinyasa Flow, Yin Yoga, Hot Yoga, meditation, pranayama, yoga philosophy, functional anatomy, teaching methodology, sequencing, and The Business of Yoga. You also participate in real classes as part of your training."
  - q: "Are payment plans available?"
    a: "Yes. You start with the Preparation Phase (3,750 DKK), and the remaining balance can be settled as a lump sum or in instalments before training begins. Your course director will discuss payment options with you."
  - q: "When do the next cohorts start?"
    a: "We run cohorts year-round: 18-week flexible starts March and August 2026, 4-week intensive in April and July 2026, and 8-week semi-intensive in May 2026."
  - q: "Is the training taught in English?"
    a: "Yes, all training is conducted in English, making it accessible to international students from around the world. Our studio is in Christianshavn, Copenhagen."
